{"title_page": "Little Love Affairs", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Little Love Affairs\n| type       = Album\n| artist     = [[Nanci Griffith]]\n| cover      = NanciGriffithLittleLoveAffairs.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1988\n| recorded   = August 1987, Soundstage Studio, [[Nashville, Tennessee]]\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[country music|Country]]\n| length     = 36:15\n| label      = [[MCA Records]]\n| producer   = [[Tony Brown (record producer)|Tony Brown]] and [[Nanci Griffith]]\n| prev_title = [[Lone Star State of Mind]]\n| prev_year  = 1987\n| next_title = [[One Fair Summer Evening]]\n| next_year  = 1988\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}} <ref>[{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r92481|pure_url=yes}} AllMusic review]</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Chicago Tribune]]''\n| rev2Score = (positive) <ref>[http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1988-02-14/entertainment/8803300323_1_nanci-griffith-love-affairs-voice Chicago Tribune review]</ref>\n| rev3 = [[Robert Christgau]]\n| rev3Score = B+ <ref>[http://www.robertchristgau.com/get_artist.php?name=nanci+griffith Robert Christgau Consumer Guide]</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev4Score = {{Rating|4|5}} <ref>[https://www.rollingstone.com/artists/nancigriffith/albums/album/126152/review/5941664/little_love_affairs Rolling Stone review]{{Dead link|date=September 2013}}</ref>\n| noprose = yes\n}}\n'''''Little Love Affairs''''' is [[Nanci Griffith]]'s sixth album, and it had similar success to the preceding album, ''[[Lone Star State of Mind]]'', on the [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] charts. The album peaked at #27 on the Country Albums chart and one of its tracks entered into the Top 40 of the [[Hot Country Singles]] chart: \"I Knew Love\" rose to #37. Two more tracks also charted: \"Never Mind\" at #58, and \"Anyone Can Be Somebody's Fool\" at #64.\n\n== LP track listing ==\n\n=== Side one ===\n#\"Anyone Can Be Somebody's Fool\" ([[Nanci Griffith]]) \u2013 2:39\n#\"I Knew Love\" ([[Roger_Brown_(songwriter)|Roger Brown]]) \u2013 3:17\n#\"Never Mind\" ([[Harlan Howard]]) \u2013 3:42\n#\"Love Wore a Halo (Back Before the War)\" (Griffith) \u2013 3:23\n#\"So Long Ago\" (Griffith) \u2013 4:10\n#\"Gulf Coast Highway\" [duet with [[Mac McAnally]]] ([[James Hooker (musician)|James Hooker]], Griffith, [[Danny Flowers]]) \u2013 3:06\n\n=== Side two ===\n#\"Little Love Affairs\" (Griffith, Hooker) \u2013 3:08\n#\"I Wish It Would Rain\" (Griffith) \u2013 2:38\n#\"[[Outbound Plane]]\" (Griffith, [[Tom Russell]]) \u2013 2:39\n#\"I Would Change My Life\" ([[Robert Earl Keen]], Jr) \u2013 3:08\n#\"Sweet Dreams Will Come\" [duet with [[John Stewart (musician)|John Stewart]]] (John Stewart) \u2013 4:25\n\n== Personnel ==\n* Charlie Bundy- background vocals\n* [[Sam Bush]] - [[mandolin]]\n* John Catchings - [[cello]]\n* [[B\u00e9la Fleck]] - [[banjo]]\n* Dan Flowers - [[slide guitar]], background vocals\n* Pat Flynn - [[acoustic guitar]]\n* Jon Goin - [[classical guitar]], [[electric guitar]]. hi-string guitar\n* [[Lloyd Green]] - [[dobro]], [[piano]]\n* [[Nanci Griffith]] - acoustic guitar, lead vocals, background vocals\n* [[James Hooker (musician)|James Hooker]] - piano, [[synthesizer]]\n* [[David Hungate]] - [[bass guitar]]\n* [[Roy Huskey Jr.]] - [[upright bass]]\n* Lucy Kaplansky - background vocals\n* [[Mac McAnally]] - [[gut string guitar]] and duet vocals on \"Gulf Coast Highway\"\n* [[Rick Marotta]] - [[drums]]\n* [[Mark O'Connor]] - mandolin, [[viola]], [[violin]]\n* [[John Stewart (musician)|John Stewart]] - electric guitar and duet vocals on \"Sweet Dreams Will Come\"\n* [[Billy Joe Walker Jr.]] - acoustic guitar\n\n== Chart performance ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Chart (1988)\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n| U.S. ''Billboard'' Top Country Albums<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/nanci-griffith/chart-history/CLP |title=Nanci Griffith Chart History (Top Country Albums)